Package: TuneBoostTreeBayesian
Title: Bayesian Tuning for Binary Boosted Tree Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Joao B. G. de", "Brito", email = "JoaoSabby@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides performance-oriented Bayesian hyperparameter tuning for binary boosted tree models with LightGBM as the primary engine and XGBoost as an alternative on a dedicated Intel Xeon Platinum 8260 host, cached stratified cross-validation, warm starts, early stopping, a Limbo ask/tell optimizer bridge, a package-native Gaussian-process optimizer fallback, and optional C, Fortran, Rfast, or base R PR-AUC scoring backends.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    cli,
    data.table,
    Matrix,
    parallel,
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
